  "text": "while a simple transformation found in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] (k i 1 + · · · + k im + k n ) [CITATION_3] and notice that only (n − 3) equations are independent due to the SL(2, C) symmetry. The polynomial form of the scattering equations is what we actually use in this paper. The Jacobian of the said transformation is simply given by a Vandermonde determinant. Notice that instead of taking σ n−1 → 1, we have replaced it with an auxiliary variable σ 0 which makes these polynomials homogeneous and obviously at σ 0 → 1 the original expressions are recovered.",
